---
import SEOLayout from '@layouts/SEOLayout.astro';
import Header from '@components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '@components/Footer.astro';
import Badge from '@components/Badge.astro';
import Card from '@components/Card.astro';
import Button from '@components/Button.astro';
---

<SEOLayout
  title="SEO Best Practices for Astro"
  description="Optimize your Astro site for search engines with these proven SEO techniques and best practices for maximum visibility."
  type="article"
  publishedTime="2026-01-30T10:00:00Z"
  author="Author Name"
>
  <Header slot="header" siteName="Astro Starter Kit" />
  
  <article class="prose section-spacing">
    <div class="text-center">
      <div class="flex gap-2 justify-center mb-4">
        <Badge variant="warning">SEO</Badge>
        <Badge variant="default">Best Practices</Badge>
      </div>
      
      <h1 class="hero-title">SEO Best Practices for Astro</h1>
      
      <div class="flex gap-4 justify-center mt-4 text-sm text-muted">
        <span>By Author Name</span>
        <span>•</span>
        <span>January 30, 2026</span>
        <span>•</span>
        <span>6 min read</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="stack mt-10">
      <p class="lead">
        Astro is built for SEO success. This starter kit includes everything you need for excellent search engine 
        visibility, but understanding the details helps you maximize results.
      </p>

      <h2>Why Astro is SEO-Friendly</h2>
      <p>
        Astro generates static HTML by default, which means search engines can easily crawl and index your content. 
        Fast loading times and clean markup give you a significant SEO advantage.
      </p>

      <Card variant="bordered" padding="lg">
        <h3>Built-in SEO Features</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Static Generation</strong> - Pre-rendered HTML for instant indexing</li>
          <li><strong>Fast Performance</strong> - Excellent Core Web Vitals scores</li>
          <li><strong>Clean HTML</strong> - Semantic markup without extra framework overhead</li>
          <li><strong>Flexible Routing</strong> - SEO-friendly URLs out of the box</li>
        </ul>
      </Card>

      <h2>SEOLayout Component</h2>
      <p>
        This starter includes a powerful <code>SEOLayout</code> component 
        that handles all essential meta tags. This blog post uses it! Here's how:
      </p>

      <Card variant="elevated" padding="md">
        <pre><code>{`<SEOLayout
  title="SEO Best Practices for Astro"
  description="Optimize your Astro site..."
  type="article"
  publishedTime="2026-01-30T10:00:00Z"
  author="Stefan"
>
  <!-- Your content -->
</SEOLayout>`}</code></pre>
      </Card>

      <h2>Essential Meta Tags</h2>
      <p>
        The <code>SEOLayout</code> automatically includes:
      </p>

      <div class="stack stack--gap-md">
        <Card variant="default" padding="md">
          <h4>Essential SEO Meta Tags</h4>
          <ul class="text-sm">
            <li>Title and description optimized for search engines</li>
            <li>Canonical URLs to prevent duplicate content penalties</li>
            <li>Author, publisher, and content metadata</li>
            <li>Structured data and schema markup support</li>
          </ul>
        </Card>

        <Card variant="default" padding="md">
          <h4>Social Media Integration</h4>
          <ul class="text-sm">
            <li>Open Graph tags for Facebook, LinkedIn, and social platforms</li>
            <li>Twitter Card support for enhanced sharing</li>
            <li>Optimized preview images and descriptions</li>
          </ul>
        </Card>

        <Card variant="default" padding="md">
          <h4>Technical SEO</h4>
          <ul class="text-sm">
            <li>Automatic XML sitemap generation</li>
            <li>Robots.txt for crawler control</li>
            <li>Clean, semantic HTML structure</li>
            <li>Fast page loads and Core Web Vitals optimization</li>
          </ul>
        </Card>
      </div>

      <h2>robots.txt & Sitemap</h2>
      <p>
        This starter includes a pre-configured <code>robots.txt</code> 
        file and automatic XML sitemap generation via <code>@astrojs/sitemap</code>. 
        The sitemap is automatically generated at build time and includes all your pages.
      </p>

      <Card variant="bordered" padding="lg">
        <h4>Sitemap Configuration</h4>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
          The sitemap integration is already configured in <code>astro.config.mjs</code>:
        </p>
      </Card>

      <h2>Performance Optimization</h2>
      <p>
        Google uses Core Web Vitals as ranking factors. Astro's zero-JS approach gives you excellent scores by default, 
        but here are additional tips:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Image Optimization</strong> - Use Astro's Image component for automatic optimization</li>
        <li><strong>Minimal JavaScript</strong> - Only add interactivity where needed</li>
        <li><strong>CSS Optimization</strong> - SCSS compiles to minimal, optimized CSS</li>
        <li><strong>Font Loading</strong> - Use system fonts or preload custom fonts</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Content Best Practices</h2>
      <p>
        Technical SEO is important, but content quality matters most:
      </p>

      <Card variant="elevated" padding="lg">
        <ul>
          <li>Write clear, descriptive titles (50-60 characters)</li>
          <li>Craft compelling meta descriptions (150-160 characters)</li>
          <li>Use semantic HTML (h1, h2, h3 hierarchy)</li>
          <li>Add alt text to all images</li>
          <li>Create valuable, original content</li>
          <li>Use descriptive URLs and internal linking</li>
        </ul>
      </Card>

      <h2>Monitoring SEO Performance</h2>
      <p>
        After deployment, use these tools to monitor and improve your SEO:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Google Search Console - Index status and search performance</li>
        <li>Google Analytics - Traffic and user behavior</li>
        <li>PageSpeed Insights - Performance metrics</li>
        <li>Lighthouse - Comprehensive audits</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="flex gap-4 mt-8">
        <a href="/blog/design-tokens">
          <Button variant="outline">← Previous: Design Tokens</Button>
        </a>
        <a href="/blog">
          <Button variant="primary">Back to Blog</Button>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
  
  <Footer slot="footer" siteName="Astro Starter Kit" />
</SEOLayout>
